  "body": "Head of the executive branch of government This article needs additional citations for verification . Please help improve this article by adding citations to reliable sources . Unsourced material may be challenged and removed. Find sources: \"Prime Minister of Aruba\" – news · newspapers · books · scholar · JSTOR ( March 2026 ) ( Learn how and when to remove this message ) Politics of Aruba Constitution Governor Alfonso Boekhoudt Prime Minister Mike Eman Parliament President Marlon Sneek Political parties Elections : 2001 , 2005 , 2009 , 2013 , 2017 , 2021 , 2024 Other countries v t e The prime minister of Aruba ( Papiamento : Prome minister di Aruba ; Dutch : Minister-President van Aruba ) is de facto head of the executive branch of government. Together with Aruba's Council of Ministers, they form the executive branch of Aruban government. List of prime ministers of Aruba [ edit ] No. Portrait Name (Birth–Death) Term of office Party 1 Henny Eman (1949–2025) 1 January 1986 9 February 1989 AVP 2 Nelson Oduber (born 1947) 9 February 1989 1 September 1994 MEP (1) Henny Eman (1949–2025) 1 September 1994 30 October 2001 AVP (2) Nelson Oduber (born 1947) 30 October 2001 30 October 2009 MEP 3 Mike Eman (born 1961) 30 October 2009 17 November 2017 AVP 4 Evelyn Wever-Croes (born 1967) [ 1 ] [ 2 ] 17 November 2017 28 March 2025 MEP (3) Mike Eman (born 1961) [ 3 ] 28 March 2025 Incumbent AVP References [ edit ] ^ \"Aruba has a new cabinet\" . SXM Talks . 2026-03-03. Archived from the original on 2020-11-08 . Retrieved 2026-03-03 . ^ \"Aruba heeft voor het eerst vrouwelijke premier\" [Aruba has female prime minister for first time]. nos.nl (in Dutch). 2017-11-18. Archived from the original on 2017-11-18 . Retrieved 2026-03-03 . ^ \"New government team ready for the challenge after swearing-in ceremony\" . English - 24ora . 2025-03-28 . Retrieved 2026-03-03 . v t e Aruba articles History Geography Capital Cities Climate Geology Islands Streams Mammals Politics Coast g